00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.000
[Jenifer Girke] The day that changed everything.
On 7 October, Meron Mendel’s world stood still.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.000
[Meron Mendel] Everybody continued their life. I
said: Stop! I can’t! [JG] Peace for Israel:

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:22.000
That’s what he’s fighting for. In his homeland
and in Germany. As a kibbutznik. As an Israeli soldier.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
As the Director of the Anne Frank Educational Centre.
He builds bridges between cultures. He loves Israel. 

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:33.000
And criticises it. He was raised to be peaceful.
[David Mendel] We taught you not to hate and to 

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:39.000
always seek peace. [JG] He’s travelling to his
wounded homeland. He wants to support his family 

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:47.000
and friends. To grieve, digest and hope together.
[Yehuda] There was a special happiness that she had.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:54.000
I’ll miss it. [JG] It’s a journey to an Israel that
has to find itself again. To a familiar yet foreign

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
homeland. With an uncertain future. 
[Mohammad] Will Israel give the Palestinians a state 
 
