00:34:06.000 --> 00:34:12.000
class. You can sense how much
Avital cares about her protégés.

00:34:13.000 --> 00:34:34.000
[children are singing]

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:40.000
[MM] It was so amazing to see them. How they love
each other. [AB] They’re pretty good children.

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:47.000
And I think they’re privileged to be together in
such a situation. [JG] The privilege of not having 

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:54.000
to hate one another. Three quarters of the 
Israeli population are Jews. Around 20% are Arabs. 

00:34:55.000 --> 00:35:01.000
Israel’s schools are generally divided 
into Arabic and Jewish. 

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:10.000
[MM] We both grew up in a segregated school
system. Why is that? [AB] I think it’s the original

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:20.000
sin of Israeli society. A Jewish child doesn’t have
the opportunity to meet an Arab child maybe until

00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:27.000
he gets to university. [JG] But many beliefs and
prejudices have already become entrenched by then. 

00:35:28.000 --> 00:35:32.000
That’s exactly what Arabic teacher Samira wants to
break down. [Samira Alhawarin] You have to know the

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:38.000
heritage of the Islamic, Jewish and Christian
cultures. Then you can move away from hate,

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:43.000
plant seeds of love and let it grow. If you
understand me and I understand you, there’s no more

00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:52.000
room for hate. Only love. [JG] The 28-year-old
sees Israel’s future through the eyes of her students.

00:35:53.000 --> 00:35:57.000
[SA] Nobody here would ever say: 'Go away! You’re
an Arab. I’m not playing with you'. Or: 'Go away!

00:35:58.000 --> 00:36:03.000
You’re a Jew'. They’re a community. So I see a
brighter future with these children. As long as

00:36:04.000 --> 00:36:09.000
they continue on that path. That will also
guide our entire country to a brighter future. 

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:15.000
[JG] And what do the children think?
[Amir] I hope there will be peace. Almost every 

00:36:16.000 --> 00:36:21.000
child in this school would say the same.
[Dania] They see that I’m Arab, so they just ask me:

00:36:22.000 --> 00:36:28.000
'Who are you with – Palestine or Israel?' 
I’m like, 'I respect everyone. I'm with neither.'

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:32.000
[Youssef (next to Yazaan)] The Jews learn our
language. And we Arabs learn their language. 

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:40.000
They learn our holidays. We learn their holidays. 
It’s just fun to be at this school. [JG] It’s words

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:47.000
like these that motivate Avital. It’s the only way
for peace to really prevail at some point. Even if

00:36:48.000 --> 00:36:54.000
there’s still a very long way to go. [MM] What we
have here is 1% of the school system. 99% is

00:36:55.000 --> 00:37:03.000
segregated. We have to turn that around. If 99%
grew up in a mixed environment, peace could truly be

00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:07.000
achieved from the ground up. [JG] Meron Mendel is
convinced that real peace building begins with

00:37:08.000 --> 00:37:18.000
education. And it’s never too late to start. 
“What’s next for my Israel?”. This question has been

00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:24.000
playing on Meron Mendel’s mind since 7 October.
The journey is coming to an end. How do you look

00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:31.000
back on the past eight days? [MM] I’ve met people
who are very close to my heart. Some of them I’ve

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:37.000
known for 30 or 40 years. There are so many things 
that unite us. And yet I’ve now seen a completely 

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:44.000
different side to them. They’ve been completely 
reshaped by the past year. And I don’t just mean 

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:52.000
7 October. They spent a year fighting for democracy.
Against the government. And since October, they’ve 

00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:57.000
been fighting for their existence. That’s what
everyone is saying. It’s our existence at stake.

00:37:58.000 --> 00:38:08.000
[JG] What kind of future do you see for Israel?
[MM] What gives me hope is the cohesion of civil

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:17.000
society. Everyone we’ve spoken to has made one point
very clear: There’s a desire for peace. Both the 

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:25.000
Palestinians we’ve spoken to, such as 
Mohammad Darawshe, and Jewish Israelis. That’s a

00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:33.000
real glimmer of hope in very dark times.
[JG] Everyone is hurting. Jews and Palestinians. 

00:38:34.000 --> 00:38:39.000
They’re united in their suffering. Therein lies an
opportunity. To make amends. To rethink Israel 

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:45.000
together. Meron Mendel has met people with
the strength and desire to do exactly that.

00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:50.000
They’ve strengthened his own belief in a peaceful
future. His homeland has rarely been so fragile. 

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:57.000
Its future is on a knife edge. He feels more connected
to the country and its people than ever before.

